{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17518011","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17518011"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T13:59:28+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T13:59:28+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12856"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"12856","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/12856"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.41,0.05,0.3,0.2]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5299"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114842"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"5299","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/5299"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12856"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96846"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"3"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"73"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"393"},{"type":"tags","id":"1115"},{"type":"tags","id":"2597"},{"type":"tags","id":"12920"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"9947"},{"type":"contributions","id":"10189"},{"type":"contributions","id":"14985"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19122"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26802"},{"type":"contributions","id":"34314"},{"type":"contributions","id":"36590"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38270"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40261"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41636"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45504"},{"type":"contributions","id":"46125"},{"type":"contributions","id":"48441"},{"type":"contributions","id":"49099"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114842","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/114842"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 76-year-old man presents to his General Practice clinic concerned about a mole on his neck that has been growing for six months. The lesion is not painful or pruritic. He has Fitzpatrick type II skin. He has a medical history of numerous solar keratoses on his arms which have been treated with cryotherapy. He has a 10-pack-year history of smoking cigarettes. An excisional biopsy with 2 mm margin is performed.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHistopathology reveals a diagnosis of nodular melanoma with a Breslow thickness of 3 mm. Further genetic testing reveals no BRAFV600E mutation. A follow-up positron emission tomography scan reveals multiple metastases to the lung.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate treatment?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Dabrafenib monotherapy","Cobimetinib and vemurafenib combination therapy","Temozolomide monotherapy","Nivolumab monotherapy","Binimetinib and encorafenib combination therapy"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThere has been an increase in the inventory of drugs available for the treatment of unresectable, stage III or IV metastatic melanoma. \u003Cstrong\u003EWhilst this is a more specialised advanced question for medical students, it is educational to be aware of the medications which can be used to treat metastatic melanoma.\u003C/strong\u003E It is also important to appreciate that treatment regimens and guidelines can and do change.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDabrafenib\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Etemozolomide\u003C/strong\u003E used to be the preferred treatment for metastatic melanoma. Dabrafenib monotherapy was used to treat metastatic melanoma with BRAFV600E mutations, whilst temozolomide monotherapy was used against metastatic melanoma in general. However, they are no longer used as monotherapy as the combination of dabrafenib with trametinib was found to be superior in a phase 3 trial. Similarly, temozolomide was superseded as it has not demonstrated improved overall survival in patients with metastatic melanoma.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECobimetinib and vemurafenib\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Ebinimetinib and encorafenib\u003C/strong\u003E therapy are still used, but they are used in metastatic melanoma with BRAFV600E mutations. Therefore, \u003Cstrong\u003Enivolumab\u003C/strong\u003E would be the preferred treatment. Nivolumab is an immune checkpoint inhibitor molecule that binds to PD-L1 on cancer cells, allowing immune cell activation and activation of antitumour immunity. Another drug that is suitable would be pembrolizumab.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Nivolumab is the preferred drug in metastatic melanoma without BRAFV600E mutation."],"references":["Long, G. V., Stroyakovskiy, D., Gogas, H., Levchenko, E., de Braud, F., Larkin, J., Garbe, C., Jouary, T., Hauschild, A., Grob, J. J., Chiarion-Sileni, V., Lebbe, C., Mandal\u00e0, M., Millward, M., Arance, A., Bondarenko, I., Haanen, J. B., Hansson, J., Utikal, J., Ferraresi, V., \u2026 Flaherty, K. (2015). Dabrafenib and trametinib versus dabrafenib and placebo for Val600 BRAF-mutant melanoma: a multicentre, double-blind, phase 3 randomised controlled trial. Lancet (London, England), 386(9992), 444\u2013451. https://doi.org/10.1016/S0140-6736(15)60898-4","Melanoma metastatic, 2023, Cancer Institute NSW, viewed 27 Sep, https://www.eviq.org.au/medical-oncology/skin/melanoma-metastatic","Boutros A, Carlino MS, Menzies AM. Melanoma medicine: New drugs for melanoma and the role of the general practitioner. Aust J Gen Pract. 2024 Sep;53(9):619-624. Available from: https://www1.racgp.org.au/ajgp/2024/september/melanoma-medicine/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96846"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12856"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96846","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/96846"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-20T20:05:33+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-20T20:06:19+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5299"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114842"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"3","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/3"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddf4","name":"Dermatology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"31","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/31"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf97","name":"Oncology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"73","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/ap